HEADWORD: Tailed
<hw>Tailed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a tail; having
(such) a tail or (so many) tails; -- chiefly used in composition;
<as>as, bob<ex>tailed</ex>, long<ex>tailed</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Snouted and <qex>tailed</qex> like a boar.</q>
<rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tailing</ent>⟦br⟧
